				\begin{document}$${{y}}_{j}={\mu }+{\alpha }x+dz+{\varepsilon }_{j}$$\end{document}yj=μ+αx+dz+εjwhere, yj is the phenotypic value for plant j (j = 1, 2 … N); μ is the model mean; x is the dummy variable for the a component taking values −1, 0 and 1 for the three genotypes; z is the dummy variable for the d component taking values 0.5 for genotype 0, or −0.5 for genotypes −1 or 1; and εik is the error term of the model. Correlation and regression analyses were implemented using SAS program30.
